LAS VEGAS, NV (LAS): DAL2580, B739, LAX-LAS, DAL2580 WAS ON THE RNDRZ ARRIVAL RUNWAY 26L TRANSITION AND REQUESTED TO DESCEND TO 10,000 FEET FOR A PRESSURIZATION ISSUE. ATC INQUIRED IF THEY WERE ON OXYGEN, AND THE PILOT REPLIED AFFIRMATIVE. DURING READ-BACKS WITH THE DAG CONTROLLER THE PILOT WAS HAVING ISSUES WITH RESPONDING DUE TO OXYGEN AND ATC DECLARED AN EMERGENCY FOR DAL2580. DAL2580 LANDED AT 0540Z AND THE PILOT CLARIFIED THAT BOTH THE COCKPIT AND CABIN WERE ON OXYGEN.11/24/2023 0544Z
